VAticinant The ſoul is ſaid to be in a vaticinant, or parturient condition, when ſhe hath ſome kind of ſenſe, and hovering knowledge of a thing, but yet cannot diſtinctly and fully, and commandingly repreſent it to herſelf, cannot plainly apprehend, much leſſe comprehend the matter. The phraſe is borrowed of Proclus, who deſcribing the incomprehenſibleneſſe of God, and the deſire of all things toward him, ſpeaks thus;
